      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The maiden stayers kick us off. BOMB PERIGNON (8) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up at the past four outings and strikes a very winnable contest here. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and should be right there when the whips are cracking. FIVE OF US (9) put in a career-best performance when second here last time out and the extra furlong should suit. Looms as the main danger. MISSILE AWAY (1) didn't handle the heavy surface at the latest effort but go on the solid second at the Sunny Coast two back. Worth another chance. STEPLIKA LION (3) has hit the top-five in eight of his past nine starts and is usually thereabouts. A must for the multiples. SEALORD (5) next best in a race with only a handful of chances.",
